                        <foliation>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>191 folios (+ 2 unfoliated parchment and 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves, both at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        </foliation>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        <collation>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>24 quires of 8 leaves each (last quire missing 1 leaf), marked with catchwords at the end, and also at the end of each of the first three leaves of ach quire.</p>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        </collation>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        <condition>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Damp at head (in part). </p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Old losses infilled. </p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Stained.</p>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        </condition>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     </supportDesc>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     <layoutDesc>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        <layout columns="1 " ruledLines="23" writtenLines="23">
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Uniform layout.</p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Titles and inital words in larger characters. First words and upward or downward strokes of letters on the first and last lines of pages respectively are sometimes ornamented, e.g., folio 81v, 82r, 136v, 137r.</p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Flesh side and hair side distinguishable.</p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>A small circle drawn on the right-hand upper corner of the first leaf of a quire, e.g., folio 33r, 41r.</p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Marginal notes.</p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Maniculae, e.g., folio 74r, 75v, 77v, 97v, etc.</p>
									
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Folio 1 is a title page.</p>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        </layout>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     </layoutDesc>
						
                  
                  
                  
                  </objectDesc>
						
                  
                  
                  
                  <handDesc hands="1">
							
                     
                     
                     
                     <summary>Sefardi square and semi-curive script of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Ḥayim Porovintsal</name> (Provenzal): inscribed with his name in the colophon, folio 184v.</summary>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						
                  
                  
                  
                  </handDesc>
						
                  
                  
                  
                  <additions>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Two additional fragmentary pieces appended: folios 185r-190v, Be᾿ur ha-melitsah, an exposition on the earlier portions of the second book of the Organon, and folios 190v-191v, Levi ben Gershom's notes 1-4 on the Intermediate Commentary of Averroes on Porphyry's Introduction to the Organon.</p>
						
                  
                  
                  
                  </additions>
						
                  
                  
                  
